Figure 4:TFA against boxed accuracy with respect to model choice on Putnam-AXIOM.We see a general positive relationship (correlation of 0.52) between the two metrics with a couple outliers. Without the two outliers the correlation is 0.62. We see an especially strong positive trend between models within in the same class (i.e. base and instruct models) which intuitively makes sense since these models are trained in similar ways.
